&lt;/span>
&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>To answer this question, we need to understand that, in a cultural sense, a mother is the one who gives birth to a child; therefore, the child comes later than the mother. Keeping that in mind, Hindi is the daughter of many North Indian languages. Let&amp;rsquo;s explore that a little further.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>